    <title>Pushes!</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#8217;ll no longer see a flood of commit events in your dashboard. Instead? Push events.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div align="center"&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.skitch.com/20081128-nn8spw31jmy5xh1f38rs2fnc3p.png" alt="" /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div align="center"&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.skitch.com/20081128-cpnb8648hsarmi127kiku7djux.png" alt="" /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;Commit events will still appear on your profile and in all your &lt;span class="caps"&gt;RSS&lt;/span&gt; feeds for now. We will be &lt;strong&gt;removing commit events&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;span class="caps"&gt;RSS&lt;/span&gt; feeds in three weeks, on &lt;strong&gt;December 18th&lt;/strong&gt;.  We&amp;#8217;ll post more about the new format soon.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update&lt;/strong&gt; Pushes with single commits now show the commit. We also fixed the wycats bug.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div align="center"&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.skitch.com/20081128-fy6x7k76rcrd3sawr76qbsaf29.png" alt="" /&gt;
