    <title>Let Me Google That For You</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Okay, it&amp;#8217;s official: &lt;a href="http://letmegooglethatforyou.com"&gt;let me google that for you&lt;/a&gt; is the new &lt;span class="caps"&gt;RTFM&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Someone on your team asks where to download solr. &lt;a href="http://letmegooglethatforyou.com/?q=download+solr"&gt;Let me google that for you&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Your friend wants to know the first man in space. &lt;a href="http://letmegooglethatforyou.com/?q=first+man+in+space"&gt;Let me google that for you&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Your boss is trying to find the best place to host code. &lt;a href="http://github.com/"&gt;Let me google that for you&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;Best of all, the code is open source and hosted &lt;a href="http://github.com/coderifous/lmgtfy"&gt;right here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
